settings.editor: Check out our NEW online classes where we explore the limits of our imagination and journey through creative adventures, to learn about the world around us.

icon_list.text: Expand our communication and interpersonal skills
Have fun and connect with new friends

settings.editor: Our teachers are all professionals in their fields and trained facilitators. Our role in class is to navigate and bring to light the most effective discussion, support everyone in the room to understand our common objective and assist the planning of how to achieve these objectives.

Finished with a 1st Class honours in Drama, Applied Theatre and Education at The Royal Central School of Speech and Drama. Has curated and conducted several outreach projects in different countries including South Africa, Honduras and Indonesia.

We offer an adaptable curriculum specially designed to fit particular needs of our participants, as well as the demands of our current times. Our content is inclusive, engaging, informed, balanced and alert. Together we will develop our interpersonal skills, grow our confidence, expand our awareness and make many friends in the process.  

Oh and of course, have an enjoyable time doing it!

Now reach our drama workshops through the screen! We use zoom to hold our meetings every day Tuesday - Friday at 4:30PM (GMT) / 11:30AM (EST) 30 minute duration until further notice. For the week’s LIVE link to the classroom or if you are interested in solo classes or have a group and want to schedule a time for your own class then please again contact us.

TRi Drama was created as an outreach company developing performing arts programs and other drama projects specific for those underserved by their society, and for those who do not have the opportunity for alternative education or education at all. Past-projects include work in South Africa, Honduras and Indonesia. We are always searching for new people and communities to work with so please contact us if you are interested in setting up a project.

All of our instructors are experts in their fields of expertise and great in transferring their knowledge 

We are taking applications for facilitators now, please send us an enquiry, your CV and a cover letter to tridramatoday@gmail.com

If you are able to donate towards TRi Drama, all money will go towards the development of our content including pre-recorded online classes you can watch any time that suits you. Your donations will also support our future outreach projects.

If you have any questions or queries please feel free to email or call

If you already have a group of children and are looking for a group online drama class please do specify this in an email including all parents emails and childrens names and ages.
